track_notes:
High ground clearance 4WD vehicle required. Very difficult and hazardous road conditions including traversing a half dozen steep ravines. Passage through 10 gates in each direction. Extremely remote area with minimal cell service. Passes required for both Federal and AZ State Land. 

I originally planned to access Eureka Mountain from the east via Eureka Springs Road off of Bonita Aravaipa Road. However, when I got to the turn-off I discovered that Eureka Springs Road is on private property and was posted NO TRESPASSING, blocking access to AZ State Land where the summit is located. I decided to explore an approach from the other side and saw that FR-693 in the Coronado NF provided an approach from the west side of the valley. My GPX track begins at the intersection of  Fort Grant Road and High Creek Road (32.58829,-109.97301) by the Bonita Elementary School. The track is 28 miles long, all of which is unpaved. Driving in took 3:21 while driving out took 2:01. Good luck! K9PM
track_title: W7A/GM-090 EUREKA MOUNTAIN--EASY HIKE, TOUGH DRIVE
